review_blob: Great session ipa! Citrusy, light bodied, crisp and clean ipa. Good hop bite! Had on tap and out of can.
beer_name: Badger State Green Chop Session IPA

review_blob: On tap. Very juicy ipa! Everything I could ever want in an ipa! Great aroma, juicy, hoppy clean palate. If I brewed an ipa I would make this every day! Damn!
On tap! Nice resin aroma. Good lacing left as I sipped this. Great hop flavor left every time I took a drink.
Bottle poured into glass. Great Citra hop aroma. Nice smooth palate, nice carbonation. very good ipa! Love asylum
Lovely piney hop aroma. Poured light and clear with minimal head. Very light palate, watery. Very nice ipa but very thin..
Sweet, maple syrup, bourbon, malty, boozy, chocolate, coffee. Great beer. Way better as it warms. Maple makes this beer
beer_name: Founders Backstage Series # 2: CBS (Canadian Breakfast Stout)

review_blob: Strong espresso taste, well balanced by the lemon peel and hops. Solid offering. Really like the 2x series from these guys!
UPDATED: MAR 8, 2015
On tap! Very nice hop aroma, well balanced malt profile. Everything a black ipa should be!
beer_name: Alaskan Pilot Series: Double Black IPA

review_blob: Out of bottle. Very nice hoppy nose. Well balanced malt profile. Good lacing on glass. Great hop forward barleywine.
Fruity and wine like. Hides the 10% well. Light and watery mouth feel. Not bad, but Im not a big lager fan
On tap. Pretty standard brown ale. Not much going on in this. Smooth mouth feel and nice lacing.
Amazing bright hop aroma. White spongey head. Light lacing on glass. Light body standard for a session. Everything you want in a session pale ale!
beer_name: Ale Asylum Demento Session Pale Ale

review_blob: Very nice hop aroma. Red in color with very nice soapy lacing that lasts throughout. Very dangerously crushable ipa
Caramel color, earthy, citrus, light malted cereal taste. Palate smooth, finish a little watery. Very nice for this style!
gift from a friend since cannot find it in wisconsin. amazing beer. lives up the the reputation. Great pale ale. Great representation of the Citra hop! One of the best pales you will find!
Pours pretty black into glass with little head. Aroma of chocolate and coffee, almost syrupy. Slight carbonation, thins out what would probably be a fuller mouth feel. Very solid, underrated stout!
beer_name: Pearl Street Thats What Im Talkin Bout Organic Rolled Oat Stout

review_blob: Good cloudy orange pour. Great hops out front. Very well balanced.  Had it at breakfast at the comet cafe in mke
Very crisp, light and bright. Great session ipa. Very hoppy front, and clean light finish
Very heavy yet crisp ipa. Great aroma and heavy mouth feel. Crisp hoppy finish. Clear beer and good head retention throughout
UPDATED: MAY 15, 2014
Great rye pale ale. Enough hops to cut the rye. Very well balanced. Like what the rye brings to the pale ale. Very crisp and bright.
Great upfront hop notes. Smooth texture. Poured from bottle to ipa glass. Great hoppy beer. Need more whole cone ipas
Poured into glass from bomber... black color nice white head. Good hop notes. Good malt notes. Good balance.
beer_name: Clown Shoes Hoppy Feet 1.5 Double Black IPA

review_blob: Very good hop aroma.... smells more like an ipa than an amber. Pours a cloudy copper color with a nice tan head. Good lacing on the glass. Very well hopped and very drinkable.
Poured from bottle. Good lacing on the glass.  Nice white head and cloudy unfiltered look.  Very hoppy all-around. One of my favorite Double IPAs
UPDATED: MAY 11, 2013
